title: For Sale/Trade:  mauser k98 small ring 8mm
postcontent: I have a very nice k98 8mm Mauser thats been sporterized a long time ago. This is a very unique mauser Its a small ring reciver in a large ring caliber and action. I have done some homework on this rifle and I believe it was originally a K98a or k98az of the First World War. The receiver was scrubbed but I can still make out three stamps on the right side that match Imperial German k98s. Also underneath the bolt handle there is an Imperial German eagle stamp. Most of the numbers on the bolt match. It appears that the original stock was cut down and had a cheek rest installed. The Stock modifications were done tastefully and still look great. This Rifle has a double trigger; one “sets” the trigger and the other fires. The double trigger is a hair trigger.
